  • Mobile phone users are suffering from a newly diagnosed condition called ringxiety. A study claims when people hear a mobile going off with a similar ringtone to theirs#Comma they get anxious and distressed when they realise the call is not for them. Ringxiety is defined as the "false belief that you can hear your mobile phone ringing".
